        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 21 at 4:48PM CDT by NWS Nashville TN</headline>
        <description>At 448 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles northeast of Linden, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pleasantville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
